name: CardiacValveSurgeriesICD10PCS
title: Cardiac Valve Surgeries ICD10PCS
purpose: (Clinical Focus: This set of values identifies patients who have a procedure of a surgery on a cardiac valve or valves.),(Data Element Scope: The intent of this data element is to identify patients who have a cardiac valve procedure.  Using the Quality Data Model, this particular element will map to the Procedure category.),(Inclusion Criteria: Only use codes which represent cardiac valve procedures. Codes used are to be ICD10PCS codes only.),(Exclusion Criteria: Exclude codes that represent a cardiac valve surgery performed using a scope.)
